  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of Lazarus</title>

    <para>
      Ensure that the source tree is in proper state:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>make -j1 FPC=/usr/bin/fpc clean</userinput></screen>

<!--
  Looks like that even multible versions (gtk3, qt5, qt6) can be on
  one machine at the same time when the binaries 'lazarus' and
  'startlazarus' are moved to
  
    lazarus      -> lazarus-gtk3
    startlazarus -> startlazarus-gtk3

  and after building the QT5 variant

    lazarus      -> lazarus-qt5
    startlazarus -> startlazarus-qt5

  and than symlink lazarus/startlazarus to the desired ones.
-->
    <para>
      If you want to build <application>Lazarus</application> with
      the gtk3 toolkit, build the package by running the following
      commands, otherwise skip the GTK instructions and proceed
      to the instructions to build the QT based variant below.
    </para>

    <para>Built GTK based IDE:</para>
<screen><userinput>make -j1 FPC=/usr/bin/fpc LCL_PLATFORM=gtk3 bigide</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now proceed to the installation (meaning skip the QT build below).
    </para>

<!-- QT5 fades out of BLFS ...    
    <para>Built Qt5 based IDE:</para>
<screen><userinput>make -j1 FPC=/usr/bin/fpc LCL_PLATFORM=qt5 bigide</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now proceed to the installation.
    </para>
-->
    
    <para>Built Qt6 based IDE:</para>
<screen><userinput>make -j1 FPC=/usr/bin/fpc LCL_PLATFORM=qt6 bigide</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Likewise, a gtk2 or a qt5 variant can be built in similar way - just use
      LCL_PLATFORM=gtk2 resp. LCL_PLATFORM=qt5 in the <code>make ... bigide</code>
      command. It is not included here as gtk2 and qt5 are outdated
      and no longer included in the BLFS book.
    </para>

    <para>
      This package does not come with a test suite.
    </para>

    <para>
      Now, install <application>lazarus</application> as the
      <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr distinstall

mv /usr/share/lazarus/docs /usr/share/doc/lazarus

mv /usr/share/lazarus /usr/lib/
for L in $(find /usr/bin -type l); do
    ln -svf "$(readlink $L | sed 's@/share/@/lib/@')" "$L"
done

sed -e 's|\(Categories\).*|\1=IDE;Development;|' \
    -i /usr/share/applications/lazarus.desktop

install -Dm644 images/ide_icon48x48.png \
       /usr/share/pixmaps/lazarus.png</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

